          <history>
            <origin>It was copied in <origDate calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1637" when-custom="1047"
              >1047 AH (1637 CE)</origDate>.</origin>
            <provenance>Signature by <persName>Muḥammad Mawṣilī</persName> on <locus
              from="Flyleaf_ia">flyleaf ia</locus>: <quote>مهمد موصلي</quote> accompanied with two
              lines of Persian poetry.</provenance>
            
            <provenance>Signature by on <locus from="Flyleaf_ia">flyleaf ia</locus>: <quote>...ابو
              الطيب ...</quote></provenance>
            <provenance>Signatures on <locus from="Flyleaf_iia">flyleaf iia</locus>: <quote>السيد
              علي الكانب</quote>, <quote>بقلم اناطولي</quote>, and <quote>عبد القادر المعروف بقدري
                زاده</quote>.</provenance>
            <provenance>Signature by Ismāʿīl bin Ibrāhīm with a seal on <locus from="Flyleaf_iia"
              >flyleaf iia</locus>: <quote> اسماعيل بن ابراهيم القاضري بمدينة
                حلب</quote>.</provenance>
            
            <provenance>Formerly part of the collection of the Persian scholar <persName
              type="standard" key="person_20108923" role="fmo">Nathaniel Bland
              (1803-1865)</persName>; see label on back paste-down: Bland No. 5.</provenance>
            
            <provenance><p>Bland’s oriental manuscripts were sold through <persName
              key="person_5679225" role="bsl">Bernard Quaritch</persName> in
              1866 to <persName type="standard" key="person_97751058" role="fmo"
                >Alexander Lindsay, 25th Earl of Crawford</persName>; his
              bookplate on the <locus from="back_paste-down">back
                paste-down</locus>: <quote>Bibliotheca Lindesiana
                  E/5</quote>.</p>
            </provenance>
            
            <acquisition>Purchased by <persName role="dnr" key="person_f6379">Enriqueta Rylands</persName> in 1901 from
              <persName key="person_9985420" role="fmo">James Ludovic Lindsay, 26th Earl of
                Crawford</persName>, for the <orgName type="corporation" role="rps"
                  ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/312795145/">John Rylands
                  Library</orgName>.</acquisition>
          </history>
          
